<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1365] TupleProtocol#writeBitSet unintentionally writes a variable length byte array</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1365</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BitSet.length() only returns the highest-set-bit, meaning that if you have more than 8 optional fields, and the 9+th optional field is unset, then only the first byte&apos;s worth of bits will be serialized. This leads to a problem on the read side, where the bit vector is assumed to be fixed width, and arbitrary deserialization occurs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
